{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}Card Game{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
    <h1>Card Game Dashboard</h1>
    <p>Welcome to the card game of the Gods! Below is a brief overview of the structure and relationships of the classes used in this application.</p>

    <h2>Class Structure</h2>
    <p>
        This application utilizes several classes to manage a card game:
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Card:</strong> Represents a single playing card, holding a suit and a value.</li>
            <li><strong>DeckOfCards:</strong> Represents a full deck of cards. It manages a collection of Card objects and includes methods to shuffle and draw cards.</li>
            <li><strong>CardHand:</strong> Represents a hand of cards. It can hold multiple Card objects drawn from a DeckOfCards.</li>
        </ul>
    </p>

    <h3>Relationships</h3>
    <p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>DeckOfCards</strong> composes <strong>Card</strong> objects, managing them through an ArrayCollection.</li>
            <li><strong>CardHand</strong> also composes <strong>Card</strong> objects, collecting cards that are drawn from a <strong>DeckOfCards</strong>.</li>
        </ul>
    </p>

    <h2>UML Diagram</h2>
    <p>Below is a UML diagram representing the relationships:</p>
    <img src="{{ asset('images/report_kmom02_uml.svg') }}" alt="UML Diagram" style="width: 100%; max-width: 600px;">

    <h2>Navigation</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><a href="{{ path('card_deck') }}">View Deck</a></li>
        <li><a href="{{ path('card_shuffle') }}">Shuffle Deck</a></li>
        <li><a href="{{ path('card_draw') }}">Draw One Card</a></li>
        <li>
            <form action="{{ path('card_draw_multiple') }}" method="get">
                <input type="number" name="number" value="5" min="1" max="52">
                <button type="submit">Draw Cards</button>
            </form>
        </li>
    </ul>
{% endblock %}
